[Article in German]

Maier W.

A prominent feature of a stable population is the stability of the age 
structure. The present investigation demonstrates that in the Federal Republic 
of Germany age distribution of youth, working population and old age pensioners 
remained stable during the last hundred years despite fluctations in the birth 
rate, death rate, and life expectancy. It can be concluded that an increasing 
life expectancy must lead to overpopulation which will in turn reduce the birth 
rate and slow down human reproduction.

